docs/architecture/v1-sectioning-and-priorities.md:165:### Why routing ships in v1.2 and not v2
docs/architecture/v1-sectioning-and-priorities.md:167:Routing contracts must exist before connectivity and coordination can make real depth/cost decisions. Deferring routing to v2 would force those packages to invent ad hoc routing assumptions that would need to be ripped out later. Routing is included in v1.2 to prevent that architectural debt.
