docs/architecture/v1-connectivity-scope.md:338:**Definition of done:** A specialist handler can emit a confidence signal, a coordinator can receive it via `onSignal`, and an escalation signal can trigger a routing mode request — all within a single in-process thread. The four workflow shapes (WF-C1 through WF-C4) are proved in integration tests.
packages/surfaces/node_modules/picomatch/README.md:518:* Bash greedily matches with negated extglobs. For example, Bash 4.3 says that `!(foo)*` should match `foo` and `foobar`, since the trailing `*` bracktracks to match the preceding pattern. This is very memory-inefficient, and IMHO, also incorrect. Picomatch would return `false` for both `foo` and `foobar`.
