packages/connectivity/README.md:1:# `@relay-assistant/connectivity`
packages/connectivity/README.md:3:`@relay-assistant/connectivity` implements the v1 in-process signaling layer for internal assistant coordination. It provides a bounded signal vocabulary, validation, suppression, lifecycle management, audience resolution hooks, and an escalation hook that routing can implement without handing routing ownership to this package.
packages/connectivity/README.md:11:- an in-memory per-thread signal log with `get()` and `query()`
packages/connectivity/README.md:15:- escalation hook interfaces that routing may implement
packages/connectivity/README.md:19:- routing decisions or mode application
packages/connectivity/README.md:21:- transport, queues, or cross-process delivery
