docs/specs/v1-surfaces-spec.md:407:Fanout is triggered when a response should reach all surfaces in a session:
docs/specs/v1-surfaces-spec.md:418:**Ordering:** Fanout sends are concurrent (Promise.all-equivalent). There is no ordering guarantee across surfaces.
docs/specs/v1-surfaces-spec.md:422:The outbound routing decision is made by core's `runtime.emit()` and delegated to the surfaces layer:
docs/specs/v1-surfaces-spec.md:425:- **Session fanout:** When `OutboundEvent.surfaceId` is absent and `OutboundEvent.sessionId` is present, `surfaceRegistry.fanout(event, attachedSurfaceIds, policy?)` delivers to all session-attached surfaces.
docs/specs/v1-surfaces-spec.md:426:- **Invalid:** When both `surfaceId` and `sessionId` are absent, core's `runtime.emit()` throws `OutboundEventError` before reaching the surfaces layer.
docs/specs/v1-surfaces-spec.md:428:This rule is defined once in `docs/specs/v1-core-spec.md` (section 3.7, `runtime.emit()` contract) and referenced here. Surfaces implements the delivery; core implements the routing decision.
