docs/specs/v1-sessions-spec.md:18:- Surface attachment — binding/unbinding surfaces to sessions; enforcing one-session-per-surface-slot rules
docs/specs/v1-sessions-spec.md:19:- Affinity — routing hint that prefers continuing an existing session over starting a new one when a returning user is detected
docs/specs/v1-sessions-spec.md:20:- Session scoping — sessions belong to a user, a workspace, or a combination; scope is recorded but not enforced by this package (enforcement is memory's concern)
