docs/specs/v1-sessions-spec.md:34:- Sessions does not persist to any specific storage backend. It defines the `SessionStoreAdapter` interface; the caller provides an implementation (in-memory, Redis, Postgres, etc.).
docs/specs/v1-sessions-spec.md:36:- Sessions does not start or stop relay connections. Surface attachment records which relay surface IDs are bound; it does not open those surfaces.
docs/specs/v1-sessions-spec.md:38:- Sessions does not fanout messages across attached surfaces. That is surfaces' concern.
